$ Registry: HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext\PersistentHandler

Apparently, setting the → Windows/registry/tree-structure/default-value of `HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext\PersistentHandler` to the → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/CLSID[CLSID] `{5e941d80-bf96-11cd-b579-08002b30bfeb}`
adds the → development/filename-extensions[extension] `.ext` to the indexer (search) service so that the contents of `*.exe` files can be found.

sa:
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT/_ext[`HKEY_CLASSES_ROOT\.ext`]
